2. CONTENT — Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International
   (CC BY-SA 4.0)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Applies to the diagnostic content: the six dimensions, the thirty questions and
their examples, the evidence signals, the design briefs, the red flags and the
0–3 rubric.

This content derives from the study by Di Dio, S., La Scala, P., Jamaldeen, B. M.,
Weigel, J. S., & Schillaci, D., "From Forecast to Decision: touchpoints, mediation,
and a formative diagnostic design grid for Climate Information Services".

You are free to share and adapt this content for any purpose, including
commercially, under two conditions:

  ATTRIBUTION — you must give appropriate credit to the authors and to this
  instrument, link to the licence, and indicate if changes were made.

  SHAREALIKE — if you remix, transform or build upon this content, you must
  distribute your contribution under the same licence as the original.

